<kml>

<concept name=Release-Resource>
<superconcept name=Action>

<hr>
<h3>Component Semantics:</h3>
  <component tag=Release-Resource>
<definition> 
to make some <conceptref name=Entity>, that is playing the <conceptref name=Role> of a <conceptref name=Resource>, available.
</definition>
</component>

<requiredslotlist>

  <slotdescription name=object>
     The <conceptref name=Resource> that's made available. It's put 
     in a <conceptref name=Be-Available> state by this action.
  </slotdescription>

</requiredslotlist>

<primaryslotlist>

  <slotdescription name=agent>
    the <conceptref name=Entity> that caused this action
  </slotdescription>

  <slotdescription name=base>
    the <conceptref name=Thing> (<conceptref name=Entity> or <conceptref name=Event>) that the object becomes available to.
  </slotdescription>

</primaryslotlist>

<neighborlist>

  <neighbor name=Release>
     In <conceptref name=Release-Resource>, the "release" signifies the "becoming available" of the resource, while in <conceptref name=Release>, it signifies the freeing of something from confinement.
  </neighbor>
  
</neighborlist>

</kml>
